At the beginning, there was a man telling us how to use a pistol. The pistol should be sounded twice. The first sound is when the bullet goes out, and the second is for reloading. In this way, it would be good to use. Therefore, that pistol should be used in this way. There is another mysterious thing, but I forgot, you asked him some questions. You said what to do if you were not sure that the pistol was loaded, and he said that you should press it when you use it. Then when I was listening to your discussion, I accidentally touched the rice cooker that my grandma was holding. I thought it would be very hot, but it wasn't. Then she asked me if I wanted chicken thighs, she said the chicken thighs were ready, and then I was going to eat chicken thighs.

I was eating a steak and just cut it up. Meanwhile you woke me up.
Let me recall. . . I was writing a song? Seems to be.

My mom and dad were arguing.
I was driving.
I was looking at a QR code, but I don't know what I was doing. However I just acted like that, staring at that QR code, but I've forgotten what happened before that.
I was at a crime scene and someone died and then. . . No more, I was there watching, I kept watching.
I was playing an arcade game.
It seems I was  the main test. The subject wanted noodles. I went to buy it for him. There was a QR code in the store downstair. I was about to take a picture of the menu and send it to the subject.

I was going to watch a play with you. I saw an episode in Empresses in the Palace where they went to eat noodles, and someone just served them. There were sofas on the left and right sides, and a table in the middle. Then I told you, these noodles were the noodles I dreamed of in the previous dream, and then you put the noodles up and recorded it.

Although the experiment was not over yet, you took my EEG-hat off. You told me that the electrodes did not work, and then asked me to wash my hair. It was only 5:30 and the experiment should go on. Then I found that you had already removed the hat, and tried it on yourself. It went all good on you. I said try the pillow, put the electrodes on the pillow to see if there is any signal.

I was watching a children's animation, "Big Ears Tutu". Tutu was playing games with his parents, his father was playing basketball, his mother was playing billiards with Grandpa Niu. Tutu was also playing basketball, but Tutu can't play , he put the basketball under the table with his cart, then the cart tripped his mother, his mother was very angry, and threw the cart away. Tutu opened the door with a basketball and entered the yard. For some reason, Tutu's mother's hand became very large. She picked up the ball and found a millipede on it.

It was funny. What's that? Robots, kinda necessary to get relief in life.
